.TH "nilfs_palloc_bitmap_blkoff" 9 "nilfs_palloc_bitmap_blkoff" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nilfs_palloc_bitmap_blkoff \- get block offset of a bitmap block
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" nilfs_palloc_bitmap_blkoff
.BI "(const struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "unsigned long group "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
inode of metadata file using this allocator
.IP "group" 12
group number
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBnilfs_palloc_bitmap_blkoff\fP returns block offset of the bitmap
block used to allocate/deallocate entries in the specified group.
